<h2>HVAC Systems for Pocatello</h2>
<p>Pocatello's cold climate demands robust HVAC systems capable of handling winter temperatures that frequently drop below freezing. For this climate zone, homeowners should prioritize high-efficiency furnaces with AFUE ratings of 90% or higher, or consider cold-climate heat pumps with HSPF ratings of 9.0 or above. Natural gas furnaces remain popular in Pocatello due to abundant local gas supplies, but electric heat pumps paired with solar panels offer an increasingly attractive alternative for environmentally conscious homeowners.</p>

<p>For cooling needs during Pocatello's mild summers, air conditioning systems with SEER ratings of 14-16 provide adequate efficiency without over-investing in cooling capacity that won't be frequently used. Ductless mini-split systems work exceptionally well in Pocatello's climate, offering zone control for the average 1,750 square foot home while providing both heating and cooling capabilities. These systems integrate seamlessly with solar installations, allowing homeowners to power their HVAC needs with clean energy throughout the year.</p>

