<p>Pocatello's diverse neighborhoods each present unique considerations for solar and HVAC installations. The historic Old Town area features charming older homes that may require electrical upgrades to accommodate solar systems, but these properties often have excellent south-facing roof orientations. Highland and Alameda neighborhoods contain many mid-century homes with simple rooflines ideal for solar panel placement and sufficient space for modern HVAC equipment.</p>

<p>Newer developments like Fairway Estates and areas near Portneuf Medical Center feature contemporary homes often pre-wired for modern electrical demands and built with better insulation standards. These neighborhoods typically see faster solar installation timelines and may require smaller HVAC systems due to improved building efficiency. Rural areas surrounding Pocatello offer abundant roof space and minimal shading concerns, making them excellent candidates for larger solar arrays, though they may require upgraded electrical service to handle substantial solar installations.</p>

