  <div><h3 class="font-bold">How much do solar panels cost in Pocatello?</h3><p>Solar panels in Pocatello typically cost between \$15,500-\$31,000 before incentives, depending on system size. After the 30% federal tax credit, homeowners pay \$10,850-\$21,700. A 6kW system suitable for most 1,750 square foot homes costs approximately \$13,020 after incentives and saves around \$770 annually on electricity bills at Idaho Power's 9.9¬¢/kWh rate.</p></div>
  
